reviews.text: Amazing place! Affordable admission! So much to see, good for the whole family!! Highly recommend! Don't forgot your coupon, you can find it on their web page.

Fun, friendly staff; good variety of cars; lots of local history.  Amazing to see all the signs, photos, hood ornaments and toys from before the 1960s. Great place to spend a few hours if you are interested in cars and their history.
You could spend hours looking around and miss a lot. Very cheep to get in 7.50 per person. Well worth it
Never knew this little place existed! So glad  I found it.  Will definitely be going back.
Awesome place. Great place to visit.  Lot neat stuff to see.
Attended veg bash to celebrate my sister's birthday. Was an expensive, rather unorganized, crowded, bazaar. Not what I expected. Parking was convenient but had to pay for it as well.
Was there for a dart tourney had a great time.
Nice place for a bridal shower but would be nice to have easier accessible restrooms!
They held OddMALL Expedition Elsewhere there.  Nice facility, lots of foot traffic.

This review is based on our visit for a wedding reception. We did not see any of the exhibits, just a heads up.

This venue is beautiful. Absolutely huge and the wedding reception we attended was about 300 people who all fit very comfortably here. The lighting made the place look very elegant and the sound from the live band was full without too much echo in such a tall room. Highly recommend using this place for a large event.
It looks beautiful from the outside. There are a surprising amount of plaques around the building so I gave myself a self tour unfortunately it was closed when I got there.

I was looking forward to visiting this museum and drove two hours to get there, only to find it closed due to the government shutdown. The closure wasn’t mentioned on their website or even the building sign, there was just a sign on the entrance to the parking lot. I encourage anyone wanting to visit to call ahead to make sure they’re open.
Great, knowledgeable staff. Enjoyed my visit, but unfortunately there were problems with an alarm and we couldn't go in the house

Nice docents and beautiful home.  they spend a lot of time talking about the Mckinley's home, life and marriage (so much more than the folks at the McKinley "library") but not much on any of the other first ladies.  The home is wonderfully restored, but it too did not belong to the McKinley's or any of the other first ladies.  None the less, it was well done and the staff are very nice.
Wonderful place to see so much herstory.  Highly recommend.

Love this place. It's great for when I need to feed the whole family or the hubby and I just want to sneak off for a fabulous tasting meal. The coffee is Amazing! The service is impeccable. Definitely a hidden treasure.

This place is great! The food was delicious, everyone working was kind, i enjoyed the atmosphere its like a cozy dinner. They had some homemade baklava too it was Amazing! Love the breakfeast food :) will be stopping by again.
This is an excellent place to eat. A very family friendly and welcoming place. With great food and service.

Such good food, amazing prices, and amazing employees/owners. So welcoming and kind. Great service and it feels so small town like everyone knows you. Will surely keep visiting even after moving out of the area. Love that they offer to go orders!!
Poor customer service, over priced for basic items and very inconsiderate. I feel like I'm eating a more expensive McDonalds only it's worse.

You have to go here! Get the Chicago Style pizza if you like pizza! Get Tiramisu if you love dessert! Don't expect anything to taste like the Olive Garden because it's not knock-off Italian food... You're going to experience a friendly, cozy atmosphere if you're dining in. If you're in a hurry though you can take it to go! Call for reservations on the weekends or at least check to see how long the wait is.

As I entered I was greeted and it made me feel welcome. As I was making  my selection the lady patiently waited to take my order.  I ordered a slice of pizza. My order came a to my satisfaction I had two slices.  The kind lady had mixed my slice up and made it up by giving them both to me. When I am down town Canton Ohio I will make sure I stop in for the best slice of pizza around.

Great food and great service. Not sure about the service experiences the low-star reviewers are complaining about. Our waitress was very kind and attentive on a busy First Friday night. We did not have a reservation and we warned by the owner that it's best to have one on First Fridays, but we were seated promptly and well taken care of.

It does state directly on the menu that food may take 45 minutes from the time of ordering, so waiting should not be a surprise to anyone. It is definitely worth the wait, though, for delicious, fresh Italian food.

AH-MAZING!!!!   The food is fantastic!  And the portions are great.  My daughter's kids spaghetti would have been enough for me!  The atmosphere is great as was the service!  We will most definitely be going back!

Absolutely loved the food. We took her two grandsons there to have dinner. We forgot to make a reservation. We had forgotten it was first Friday. They seated us immediately helped us. They didn't become upset when our little guy started having a tantrum because he was hungry. Food was served was quickly efficiently and tasted amazing. Definitely one of our favorite spots to eat. I highly recommend this place if you're ever in the Canton area. Live music on First Fridays. Definitely a great experience. Our guy love the live music.

I've been here twice so far and had excellent meals. This is Canton's oldest restaurant and there's no surprise why...great food! 

Our server was very friendly and explained how they get their fish fresh from Boston three times a week. I had the Yellowtail Tuna with light Cajun seasoning and it was cooked perfectly (medium rare) and very tasty. My date got Turtle Soup and Grey Sole Fillet. I sampled both and they were outstanding. One of my sides was the Bender fries, which is flattened and grilled (kind of like hash browns). While it was tasty, it had a little too much oil on it. Not sure how it's prepared.

Parking lot is right across from the restaurant and if that fills up there's always street parking.

Get reservations if you're going on the weekend as it's a popular spot!

I love walking in and seeing Michael’s face. It is such a breath of fresh air that there are people so dedicated to serving the public.  He is so polite and full of life. I remember how bad he felt my first time i was In there when he dumped the chicken Marsala in my lap. Because he trip over his shoelace. Still go ther till this day.
Lovely setting. Excellent staff. Kind and helpful. Pricey but worth it. Definitely recommend to anyone visiting Canton!

I have never had a bad experience at this restaurant.  The Walleye tonight was simply amazing.  Even the salad was good and that says a lot coming from a non green lover!  My wife had Chilean Sea Bass and she loved it!!!

Food and service is great.  Have gone for lunch for years and have never been disappointed.  First dinner time visit. You would expect that when you pay twice as much for the same meal at dinner,  the portions would be larger. Not the case at all.  It was so underwhelmed when i saw my meal come out,  that I immediately ordered another side as soon as the waitress put it down. 

Again, the food and service was great,  but save yourself a ton of money and go and go at lunchtime. I will never go back at dinnertime.
